    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you live alone in a house and due to some reason go out then after coming back to your door you should not ring the doorbell as you do when we go to other’s hours. We open the door. Nobody will open your door from inside because the insider has gone out and there is no one inside. We all understand this simple logic but when we need to apply this to our spiritual dimension of living we fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
